\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Words should wander and meander. They should fly like owls and flicker like bats and slip like cats. They should murmur and scream and dance and sing.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Sometimes there should be no words at all.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Just silence.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Just clean white space.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
Some pages will be like a sky with a single bird in it. Some will be like a sky with a swirling swarm of starlings in it. My sentences will be a clutch, a collection, a pattern, a swarm, a shoal, a mosaic. They will be a circus, a menagerie, a tree, a ne
