\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 The locked steel gate was close behind her.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Yes, Mum,\'94\loch\f0  I said.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Are you certain?\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Yes, Mum.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 I wonde\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 red if I should tell her the tale of the day I went through the steel gate all alone. I didn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t. When I think about it, there\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s quite a few things I don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t tell her about. Like most kids, I suppose. Sometimes it\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s best just to keep things to myself because \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 I\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0  don
\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t want to upset her. Sometimes they\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 re just too weird to explain. Sometimes I just don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t know how to get the words out. It doesn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
t matter. I guess she knows there\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s lots of things she doesn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t know about me. But it doesn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t matter. You don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t have to kn\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 o
\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 w every single thing about a person in order to understand them.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 She smiled and hugged me.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 You\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 re a strange one,\'94\loch\f0  she said as we walked on.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 I know,\'94\loch\f0  I said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ll write the story of the Underworld for her and maybe I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ll let her read it. Somehow it might m\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 ake more sense if it\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s written down.
