She was just nine years old. She was very skinny and very small and she had jet-black hair and a pale pale face and shining eyes. \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
Some folks said she was weird. Her mum said she was brave. Sometimes she seemed very old for her age, and sometimes she seemed just like a little girl. All those things were true. She felt so strong and bold, lonely and lost, and the world seemed very big
\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
and she seemed very small. Her mum said that everybody felt like that at some time in their lives, no matter how old they were, but that for Mina it was more difficult because of what had happened to her dad. She said that as Mina grew, she\hich\f0 
\rquote \loch\f0 d feel stronge\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 r\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0  more often and not feel so small.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Mina\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s mum was strong. To Mina she seemed brave and gentle. She had glossy red hair and dark green eyes and Mina thought that if there was such a thing as a saint in this world, then her mum was one.

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 In the past, Mina had\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0  heard her mother arguing with doctors, especially with the doctor who talked about giving pills to Mina, pills that he said would make her feel better.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 They won\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t make her feel better!\'94\loch\f0  said Mina\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s mum. \'93\loch\f0 They\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
ll stop her from feeling anything at all. She\loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s not some kind of robot. She\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s a little girl that\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
s growing up and she can do that without your stupid pills!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Mina\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s school was St. Bede\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s Middle, very close to the park. It was a Monday morning in spring. The lesson was called History. The teacher, Mr.\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
 Henderson, talked about the city\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s past. He said that once the city had been surrounded by coal mines. For hundreds of years, men and boys had gone down into the earth to dig out coal. Imagine that, he said. He laughed. Imagine going into the pitch darkn\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 e
\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 ss to bring out stuff as black and bright as Mina McKee\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s hair. He said that if they could travel into the earth beneath the classroom, they would discover a warren of shafts and tunnels. His eyes widened. They might even discover the bones of those who h\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 a
\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 d died down there. He said that the days of the coal mines had been very perilous, but people had lived and worked together, and shared their tragedies and joys.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 He read some poems about pitmen, and played their songs on a CD player. He sang some pitmen\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
songs himself. He said that his own grandfather had been a pitman, and that he had been brought up with tales of the underground, of the men who traveled deep into the earth every day, of ponies they had down there, and of the ghosts they said they had se
\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 e\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 n down there.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 He showed them maps of the city as it used to be. There were pit shafts that plunged hundreds of feet down into the earth. There were tunnels that crept from the city\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s fringes towards its heart. He said that very close to the school, in Hest\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
on Park, there was an entrance to a tunnel that once was used to carry carts of coal from the coal mines down to the river. He said the tunnel was being repaired. There were plans to reopen it for tourists and for those who wanted to study the city
\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s past.\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0  Maybe when it opened, he said, they\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 d all go into the tunnel together on a class trip. Then the lesson ended.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Mina already knew about the entrance and the tunnel. She\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 d seen the ancient solid steel gate behind some rhododendron bushes. She\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 d seen the gird
\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 ers welded across the gate. Recently, she\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
d seen that the girders had gone. Men wearing hard hats and carrying big torches went into it. There was a new orange sign there. It said DANGER KEEP OUT and there was a skull and crossbones symbol on it.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 In Mina\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0  mind, the gate, the tunnel, and now Mr. Henderson\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s stories mingled with many other stories that she\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
d heard \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0  stories from ancient times about heroes and heroines who lived in the underground: Daedalus, who built an underground maze with a monster calle\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 d\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
 the Minotaur at its heart; Pluto, the King of the Underworld, and Persephone, his wife; stories about the dead, who were taken from this world to live in the darkness below. And they mingled with the tale of Orpheus, the greatest singer in the world, who
\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 s\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
e beautiful wife, Eurydice, was killed by a venomous snake. Orpheus would not accept her death. He traveled the world, searching for the entrance to the Underworld. When he found it, he went down into the Underworld, and begged for her to be given back to
\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 him.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
Mina knew it was silly, but she was only nine years old, and she was often very sad, and in her imagination and in her dreams, the entrance to the Underworld was there, behind the rhododendron bushes, in Heston Park. And she told herself she\hich\f0 
