\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 I am,\'94\loch\f0  I said.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Good lass!\'94\loch\f0  He grinned, and shrugged, like he wanted to say something but didn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t know wha\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 \hich\f0 t to say. Then he just called out, 
\'93\loch\f0 Live your life, young\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 n!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 And he was gone, carrying the remnants of Mr. Myers\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s life to the town dump.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 What else can I do but live my life? But of course he meant, Live it well. Live it to the full. Which is a very nice \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 thing to say to anybody, and which is exactly what I intend to do!
