\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 And his smell must remain as well. And maybe they were the stains of his\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0  pee on the floorboards. Maybe there were molecules of Mr. Myers\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s breath still mingling with the air inside the house. Maybe his soul was still inside the house.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 In some places, people believe that a person\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s soul stays near their home for many days after\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
 death before it flies away. In some places people believe that the soul never leaves this world, but takes the form of a bird. Imagine if that were true \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0  that the birds we see around us are people\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s souls. I looked up to the roof, where a blackbird was \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 c\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 alling. I held my hands against the brightness of the sky. Much higher up, I saw the tiny black dots of distant singing larks.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Then Mum was there, behind me. She put her hand on my shoulder.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 Wish I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 d known him when he was young,\'94\loch\f0  I said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Mum laughed.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 If \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 you had, you\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 d be well on the way to being an old woman yourself.\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  I pondered that fact. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
He was a nice bloke,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Mum said. \'93\loch\f0 I always remember pushing you along in the buggy and he opened the door and came out. He put a pound coin into your hand. A bit of t\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 r
\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 \hich\f0 easure for the baby, he said.\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Was Dad there?\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Yes. Yes, he was.\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  Then Mum flinched. \'93\loch\f0 What\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s that?\'94\loch\f0  she said.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 What\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s what?\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 That. Inside the house, Mina.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 We both peered in through our hands, and we saw the black cat slinking out of the room through th\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 e open door.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Oh,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  she breathed. \'93\loch\f0 It\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s just a cat.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 I smiled at the image of my little savage friend. I was certain there\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 d be mice aplenty for him in Mr. Myers\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s empty house.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 There\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s been people looking at the house already,\'94\loch\f0  I said.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Good. Be nice to have new neighbors soon.\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 But they might be boring,\'94\loch\f0  \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 \hich\f0 I said. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 They looked very boring.\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 You know you can\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t tell what somebody\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s like just by looking at them, Mina.\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 Yes, I know that. But they did look boring, and\~\hich\f0 \'85\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 She laughed.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 Maybe you should put a notice on the door. Only interesting people are allowe\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 \hich\f0 d to buy this house!\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Maybe I should.\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 Anyway, buying a house is very complicated, and whoever buys this one will need to do lots of work, and that\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ll put people off, so just because somebody\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s looking at it doesn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t mean anything.\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 I know.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 A blue car d\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 
rove slowly past. The man driving it peered out. He stopped the car. The woman beside him leaned right down so she could see it too. She soon sat up again. They said a few words, he drove away.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 Be nice if a family bought it, wouldn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t it?\'94\loch\f0  said Mum.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 I shru\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 gged.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 Be nice if they had somebody round about your age, wouldn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t it?\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 Don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t care,\'94\loch\f0  I said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 She smiled gently.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 Don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t you?\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 No. Just as long as they\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 re\~\hich\f0 \'85\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Interesting?\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Yes! Interesting!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 She smiled again and I suddenly felt really awkward. She reache\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 d out and patted my arm.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 m sure they will be,\'94\loch\f0  she said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 We walked back home. The blue car drove into the street again and went slowly past the house again.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 The blackbird squawked a warning call.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Do you believe that birds are souls?\'94\loch\f0  I asked.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 She ponde\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 red.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 No. Not really. It\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s a nice thought, though. Do you?\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 No. Birds are quite extraordinary enough without having to be souls as well.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Mum went back into the house. I climbed back into the tree.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 The blackbird watched me. I watched the man and the woman get out of the blue car. They went to Mr. Myers\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s window. The woman appeared to be pregnant. They looked very nice.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 Are the eggs here yet\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 \hich\f0 ?\'94\loch\f0  I whispered to the blackbirds.
