 believe that if you have not lived well you will be reborn as an insect, or even as a vegetable.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Or as a fruit?\'94\loch\f0  I said, holding up my banana.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Yes, some people believe you could be reborn as a banana. Or as a pea, or a Brussels sprout.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 I bit the banana.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 I wouldn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t like to be a sprout. But a banana! Imagine being such a color and having such a taste!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 I bit the banana again. If there was a soul inside it, would you taste it? Or was the soul\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s taste the essence of banananess?
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 Maybe good souls turn out b\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 \hich\f0 right and tasty,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  I said. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 And bad souls turn out being green and yuck!\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Maybe. Then raspberries, for instance, must be very good souls. And if you became an insect, what would a good soul be?\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 A dragonfly,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  I said. \'93\loch\f0 Imagine being able to do what a drago\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 \hich\f0 nfly does and to look like a dragonfly looks.\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Or a good soul could turn out to be a bee.\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 To be a bee,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  I said. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 To be a bee!\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 And a bad soul?\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 A cockroach.\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 A bluebottle.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 I pondered.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 d quite like to be a bird,\'94\loch\f0  I said.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 I can imagine you as a bird.\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 A skylark, flying so high it can\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t be seen. Or a cat, as black as the night.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 We were quiet for a time. We got on with our lunch. I tried to imagine what Dad might like to be, and I cam\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 e up with a horse, a beast that\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s strong and fast and beautiful and proud. I didn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t want to imagine him as another human being. The only human being I wanted him to be was my dad, even if he was just a memory of my dad.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Another word for transmigration,\'94\loch\f0  s\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 \hich\f0 aid Mum, \'93\loch\f0 is metempsychosis. It\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s a word from ancient Greece.\'94

