\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Hello, Grace.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 She smiled and reached across the garden wall and took my hands\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0  in hers. Her hands were bony, dry and cold.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 She winked at me.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ve seen you in your tree, Mina. You look quite at home up there.\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 I am.\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 I used to love climbing, when I was a girl. I used to dream of climbing trees all day, stepping and swinging from o\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 \hich\f0 ne to the next, never once coming down to ground.\'94

\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Did you ever do it?\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 Not enough trees, Mina. But I made a lovely little circuit in my garden. From the corner of the outhouse, onto the apple tree, onto the top of a wobbly stepladder, then back to the o
\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 \hich\f0 uthouse again.\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  She lifted her foot and giggled and groaned. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 And these days I can hardly get up the blooming stairs.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 An icy gust of wind blew along the street. She winced.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Sometimes you look sad up there in your tree,\'94\loch\f0  she said.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Do I?\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 Yes. But sad\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 all right. Sad\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s just part of everything.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 She winked.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Persephone!\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  she hissed. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Come on!\'94\loch\f0  She said it again as if she was singing a little song, and I joined in with her.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 Come on, Persephone!
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Come on, Persephone!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 She moved her hips like she was dancing\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0  and I joined in with her. She groaned softly and gritted her teeth and closed her eyes. Then she grinned.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Bad bones,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  she said. \'93\loch\f0 But never mind. They\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ll be fixed up soon and then\~\hich\f0 \'85\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Suddenly she put her hand to her mouth.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Goodness gracious!\'94\loch\f0  she said.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 What is it?\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 I just remembered, all of a sudden. I dreamed about you last night.\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 About me?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 She laughed.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 Yes. You were in your tree and you said, Come on up here, Grace! So I climbed up beside you. You had tiny little feathers on you, just like a baby\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 \hich\f0 
 bird. Like a fledgling! Goodness gracious, we both did!\'94
