s night. No stars. Mist is hanging in the street. Frost is glittering. \'93\loch\f0 IT\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 S SUPPOSED TO BE SPRING!\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  I want to yell. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 SO GET LOST, FROST!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 An owl hoots, from the direction of Mr. \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Myers\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s house. It hoots again, and something hoots in answer.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Owls. I feel so close to them. I share a home with them.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Good night, owls,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  I whisper. \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll write your story tomorrow.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Hoot. Hoot hoot hoot.
