\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 d heard a lot about me. I don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t think I said anything to him. I read the program while they prattled and drank and nibbled peanuts. The play was Grimm Tales. I do remember I thought about talki
\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 n\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 g about whether wolves really were as savage as they\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 re made out to be in the fairy tales. But I didn\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t, and they prattled on.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Remember him?\'94\loch\f0  Mum says again.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Not sure if I do,\'94\loch\f0  I say.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 She grins.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll be off to the tree,\'94\loch\f0  I say.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Go on, then.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 I head for the door. I hesitate there.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 What did he want?\'94\loch\f0  I say.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Just to say hello.\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Took a long time to say hello.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 I go out and close the door.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Huh! Colin Pope!
\par 
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 m in the tree. The leaves are thickening fast. I check the eggs. Still there, still thr\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 ee of them, still beautiful.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Squawk squawk, go the blackbirds.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 OK,\'94\loch\f0  I whisper back.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 I sit on my branch, surrounded by thickening leaves. Soon I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 ll be quite hidden away up here. I turn my mind back towards the past.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 They sent a red taxi to take me to Corin\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 thian Avenue \hich\f0 \endash \loch\f0 
 maybe to make sure I went at all. Mum came with me that morning. The taxi driver was wearing a yellow football strip with PEL&#201; written across the back.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 He kept looking at me in the driver\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s mirror as we set off.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 Do you take many to Cor\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 \hich\f0 inthian Avenue?\'94\loch\f0  I asked him.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 Sure do. Got a contract. I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ve took quite a crew to Corinthian Avenue in my time, I can tell you.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 He drove on, past the park, through the slow-moving traffic towards the city center.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 And I could tell a tale or two,\'94\loch\f0  he said.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Tell one,\'94\loch\f0  I said.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 No chance.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 He shook his head. He took a hand off the steering wheel and tapped his nose.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Confidentiality,\'94\loch\f0  he said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 He wound the window down and leaned an elbow on the frame.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 More\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 n my job\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s worth,\'94\loch\f0  he said.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 The traffic thickened, \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 edged through the streets past the offices and shops. We drove slowly onto the bridge. The arch arced beautifully above us. The river sparkled beautifully below.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 I caught him watching me again.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 So what\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s your story?\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  he said. \'93\loch\f0 If you don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t mind me asking,\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 \hich\f0  that is?\'94

\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Sorry?\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 Tell me to shut up and stop prying if you like. But some kids like to get it off their chest with a bloke like me. And whatever you say\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll stay within these cab walls.\'94

\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 I looked at Mum. She looked at me.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 I think we\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll just keep it to ourselves, thank you very much,\'94\loch\f0  said Mum.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 It\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s OK, Mum,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  I said. \'93\loch\f0 I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 m sure Mr. Pel&#233; will keep it secret.\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 It\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s Karl,\'94\loch\f0  said Karl.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 OK,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  I said. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 It was violence, Karl.\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Get away,\'94\loch\f0  said Karl.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 It\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s true. I attacked a t\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 \hich\f0 eacher.\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Aye?\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Aye. With a pen.\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 A pen?\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 Aye. It made a great weapon. I stabbed her in the heart. I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 m really vicious once I start. I don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t look like it, but I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 
m a bloody savage!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 I snarled into the mirror. I bared my teeth. Karl raised his eyebrows. He\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0  shook his head. He whistled softly.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Goes to show.\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Goes to show what?\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 That you never can tell.\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 That\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 s what I think as well. You never can tell.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 He drove on slowly in silence.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 She asked for it,\'94\loch\f0  I said.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Aye?\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 Aye. She went on and on. Yak yak yak.\loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Yak yak yak?\'94\loch\f0  said Karl.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Yes. Yak yak yakkity yakkity yak yak yak.\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 I had a teacher like that,\'94\loch\f0  said Karl.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Was she called Mrs. Scullery?\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 Nah. It was a bloke. Blotter, we called him. Can\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 t remember his real name.\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 But he went yak yak yak?\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 Aye. He\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 \hich\f0  had more of a snarl in it, though. So it was like more vicious. Yek yek yekkity yek! That kind of thing.\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Did you attack him?\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 Naah. He was a great big bloke, and I was just a titch. He had a hell of a temper, and all. So I just shut me lugs and let him\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 \hich\f0  get on with it. Yek yek yek yekkity yek.\'94

\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 Pity. Anyway I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 d had enough of Mrs. Scullery and her yak yak yak, so I done her.\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 With the pen.\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Aye. I done her good, with the pen.\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Murder?\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 Not quite. She\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 ll survive.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 I looked down at the water that flowed beneath us toward the sea. I said,
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Are you as good as Pel&#233;, Karl?\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 He grinned.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Aye,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  he said. \'93\loch\f0 In fact, I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 m even better.\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Really?\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 Really. You should have seen the goal I scored in the park last week. Breatht\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 \hich\f0 aking.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 We grinned at each other in the mirror.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 So why are you driving taxis?\'94\loch\f0  I said.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 Cos I love it. Who\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 d want to travel the world and make a million quid and be adored by all them fans? No, it\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s journeys to Corinthian Avenue for me! And look, here we \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 \hich\f0 are, safe and sound.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 He stopped the car and opened the door to let me out.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 He pretended to flinch as I stepped out. He put his hands up as if to protect himself.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 I laughed and he grinned.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Keep them pens under control today,\'94\loch\f0  he said.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 I will.\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 See ya, M\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 \hich\f0 iss. Savage.\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Bye-bye, Mr. Pel&#233;.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 He winked at us and drove away.
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 And there it was, a redbrick house surrounded by Tarmac and a steel fence, and tubs with blue hydrangeas in them.
\par 
