\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Anyway,\'94\loch\f0  she says. She does a couple of \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 \hich\f0 jumps on the pavement. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 I just wanted to show you my limplessness!\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 She jumps and jumps again.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Limplessness,\'94\loch\f0 \hich\f0  I whisper. \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Limp-less-ness!\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Not bad, eh?\'94\loch\f0  says Sophie.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 No. Not bad. Very good.\'94
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 And I just wanted to say hello. And now goodbye.\'94
\par \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 Then she\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s \hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 gone. I say goodbye after her. I want to jump down and run after her and grab her and tell her she\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s nice, too, and that I\hich\f0 
\rquote \loch\f0 m very pleased for her, and that\~\hich\f0 \'85\~\loch\f0 But I don\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 t. She goes back to her friends. I close my eyes.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Stupid Mina!\'94\loch\f0  I squeak to myself.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 Sh\hich\af0\dbch\af31505\loch\f0 \hich\f0 e wonders about me,\'94\loch\f0  I squawk softly.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 She says I\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 \hich\f0 m nice,\'94\loch\f0  I whisper.
\par \loch\af0\dbch\af31505\hich\f0 \'93\loch\f0 \hich\f0 Limplessness,\'94\loch\f0  I murmur, and I slowly write two lovely words in my book.
